      "commit": {
        "parents": [
          {
            "commit": "298cdb5c0b6136b91e76c9c515bfbc2df99bae0b",
            "subject": "LU-12999 mgs: Cleanup string handling in name_create_mdt"
          }
        ],
        "author": {
          "name": "Mr NeilBrown",
          "email": "neilb@suse.de",
          "date": "2019-11-24 23:00:48.000000000",
          "tz": 660
        },
        "committer": {
          "name": "Oleg Drokin",
          "email": "green@whamcloud.com",
          "date": "2019-12-16 06:00:05.000000000",
          "tz": 0
        },
        "subject": "LU-12678 lnet: discard lnd_refcount",
        "message": "LU-12678 lnet: discard lnd_refcount\n\nThe lnd_refcount in 'struct lnet_lnd' is never tested (except\nin an ASSERT()), so it cannot be needed.  Let's remove it.\n\nEach individual lnd keeps track of how many lnet_ni are\nregistered for that lnd e.g. ksocklnd has a counter in ksnd_nnets\nand o2iblnd has a linked list in kib_devs.\nThey hold a reference on the module while there are registered\ndevices, and the lnd is only freed (and the lnd_refcount checked)\nwhen the module is unloaded.  This confirms that lnd_refcount\nadds no value.\n\nSigned-off-by: Mr NeilBrown <neilb@suse.de>\nChange-Id: I0d0c04051bf01a1fa77d888b00fb0a7875b09ccd\nReviewed-on: https://review.whamcloud.com/36829\nTested-by: jenkins <devops@whamcloud.com>\nTested-by: Maloo <maloo@whamcloud.com>\nReviewed-by: Serguei Smirnov <ssmirnov@whamcloud.com>\nReviewed-by: James Simmons <jsimmons@infradead.org>\nReviewed-by: Chris Horn <hornc@cray.com>\nReviewed-by: Amir Shehata <ashehata@whamcloud.com>\nReviewed-by: Oleg Drokin <green@whamcloud.com>\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/master"
    }
  },
